TOP researchers at the University of Limpopo were given excellence awards on Friday at the Fusion Boutique in Polokwane.They won prize money – and then the university’s vice-chancellor, Mahlo Mokgalong, doubled it.The overall winner, Professor Tebogo Mothiba, walked away with R120 000 for her research in health services.“We are rewarding you for the good work that you are doing at our university.“You have done your research in an excellent way and we are proud of you,” said Mokgalong.Dr Manyane Makua, a former lecturer at the university, is now director of teaching and learning development at the Mangosutho University of Technology in KwaZulu-Natal.He said some of the researchers have battled and overcome the odds in their lives, including social disadvantage, inequality and poverty.“Our university should never forget the students they admit, and not neglect the responsibilities of providing academic support to compensate for the lack of such capital.”He suggested the university give researchers space to develop further.He said students should be provided with student assistants to reduce the workload.“That’s one way to encourage the academic excellence that we have seen tonight.”if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvXwZvDTMnXGdHwWGC-rdPXmvQxCA9DIUlqw3EnvpqYWSrWfk_aitYA376vgndpQ7tzxYqAkCQyH4pcga1yL26mVsTW9jN_PO1BTfCyzXAFYBJ2bLd2INyPC4eHLFBLv8A8i_SuWMY4CPsWhSMmIlcZ9VpmFmjXOSjEdTXvHtB02YJHAp3VDYzLCyZ86jOaeDL5AXPBIjJ3sZ_vOUftTiK6ePiHBIG-sodPYtjVQHS1TzPszgypsCJUB2knuhcmoGbZCsv9jPL9nGruipT-VTK-fRKOTAc\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzBGOg61ip1-iEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
